<br />
It was a good idea, but NOT when SoE keeps stealing the elemental tag on more and more mobs, NOT when the minimum level for the charm is inferior to that of Enchanters, and again, NOT when the Charm is usable to gain experience in a SINGLE zone for a level 65 mage.
<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Unless it is made perfectly clear that the elemental dire charm will not work like the enchanter, necromancer or druid one,</span> and that it will let us charm mobs of an exceedingly higher level, AND that we will see addition of summoned mobs all around the game, please, brothers, let us be clear that we do not want something that will rot as Mass Group Buff, Turn Summoned or Frenzied Burnout.
<br />
I know this might ultimately be futile, that if they do want to put the ability in game, it will be put in game. What I hope is to see all my brother mages rise and denounce how much of a bad idea this is.
<br />
Let us make sure that we get it replaced by something else - something like what the BSTs seem to be getting, and that is AAs that will improve our summoned pets.
<br />

