			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">at least it's not another int caster class =P
<br />

<br />
And it does indeed seem our AA's suck once again. We've only had one or two good aa's really. Let me take a critical view on Our current aa's:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Pet Discipline </span>- one of the two useful aa's we have, and it's shared by pretty much most pet classes. 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mass Group Buff</span> - Come on now...really... One buff that lasts 9 mins max with a recast of 1 hour 12 minutes, and that one spell isn't really even useful because the entire raid doesn't normally get hit unless something goes terribly wrong, in which that Ds won't help much.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Elemental Form : fire</span> - useful untill level 65, which the spellcasting cap is max'd at and can't be raised anymore. That and there aren't a ton of indoor zones outside of Ldon where one would use elemental forms instead of a mount.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Elemental Pact </span>: Pets over 60 cept the air pet don't use them anyway, making this a useless ability.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Frenzied Burnout</span> - Was useful sorta when it was bugged and we could have unlimted frenzy on charmed pets, but even then it was limited to the one zone we could use it in. 100% haste for 30 seconds on pets doesn't help much and RAMPAGE and FLURRY don't do much either. 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Improved Reclaim Energy</span> : ... it's obvious the problems this AA causes just by reading the numerous posts about it on the forum. it messes up pet canni and can't be turned off.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mend Companion</span> - useful? sorta... but not to much extent it's a free pet in dire circumstances, but most people would prefer to just chain pets.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Quick Summoning</span>  ; Again, useful but only as a novelty or as a mage in VT. Summoning items faster doesn't help us really and cohing faster is the only thing it's useful for, and there aren't many palces where that would be used nowadays.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Turn Summoned</span>  : Only use I ever found for it was in trials in PoV when you had an excess number of rocks spawn.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Elemental Form : Earth</span> : useful in raids, more hp and such, but eh.. not worth the aa points it costs to get max'd, extra 200hp or so? payed less points for Durability.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Elemental Form : Air</span> - Resists are nice but again, is it worth the points? More resist bonus's for training general ability resists for less points.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Elemental Form : Water</span> : Extra mana regen, but again at least in the high end game, most mages will find they aren't limited by mana pool but rather aggro. 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Fury of Magic</span> : Ok, this one is useful also. More chances are crits are always nice to have. but it's shared by all int casters so it's nto a class AA.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Hastened Banishment  </span>: Yes, for the one time I can think of to use it...
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Hastened Mending</span>  : Yes and no, it can be useful if you like healing pets, but eh...
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Host of the Elements</span>  : Outclassed by shaman swarm pets. Making them half the number of our swarm but half the recast time makes them even, but add in they're higher level (so hit more and have more hp) but they enrage also and it's fairly obvious to see..
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Innate Defense</span>  :  useful sorta, every int caster has it again though, so can't base anything around it.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Lightning Reflexes</span>  : Same as above.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mastery of the Past </span>: Only spell I cast below level 62 is gate coh and mod rods, don't know about you guys...
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Servant of Ro</span> : Useful yes, but very limited dps, even with the upgrade.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Suspended Minion</span> : one of the few class aa's that are useful to us. This one is nice to have in alot of circumstances and it worth the points put into it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Feel free to correct anything I said above as it was wrote in a hurry because I have to be at work in a few mins and didn't have time to check and research things and make sure they were all still true.
<br />

<br />
Sony, you need to look at our aa's and think to yourselves, would you want them or something that other classes have?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
