				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Quotes from Hobie:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Mend Companion - useful? sorta... but not to much extent it's a free pet in dire circumstances, but most people would prefer to just chain pets. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I think you are being way too negative here.  Mend Companion is a fantastic AA.  One of my best.  Having an instant cast heal for 2146 allows me tons more safety for soloing/grouping/raiding.  I always know I have an ace in my pocket to get me out of a bad situation if needed.  Or to at least give me time to gate.  If I'm using it every 9 min, then it saves my mana and gives me a much better efficientcy for pet tanking.  And as for chained pets...  (Fully buffed and Equipped pet) >>> (Chain casted pet with BoV) 
<br />
Yes I love to chain cast pets too, I was one of the original mages that did this kind of tactic way back in the days before Kunark.  But some fights are NOT better with chained pets.  Many times it's better to have one pet up, fully buffed and equipped and heal him.  There is a breaking point where one tactic becomes better then the other, and it all comes down to final Kills/Time, and mana Efficientcy.  You seem to be very negative on our pet heals.  While I think they are great.  I run full focus on my pet heals and I have Hasted Mending 3.  Between those my pets stay alive very easily with very little mana.  And when I run into a mob that is immune to spells I'm a FAR BETTER MAGE then another who does not have fully focused heals, and Mend Companion.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Quick Summoning ; Again, useful but only as a novelty or as a mage in VT. Summoning items faster doesn't help us really and cohing faster is the only thing it's useful for, and there aren't many palces where that would be used nowadays. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This ability has also been very valuable to me.  Extremely valuable actually.  Quick Summoning 2 is what most mages need to get their pets down to 5 seconds for canni.  Not just canni though, when I have a mob beating me down, casting a 5 second pet gives me a MUCH better chance to channel through getting hit.  6 second CoTH has literally saved raids from hours of downtime for me.  When that puller is about to die and I zip his ass right out of the fire.  Every puller death can be an added 15-20 min for corpse pull, rez, rebuff, and next pull.  Finally, when I'm summoning tons of items when I first log in it's very nice to have the cast time so much faster.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Elemental Form : Air - Resists are nice but again, is it worth the points? More resist bonus's for training general ability resists for less points. 
<br />
Elemental Form : Water : Extra mana regen, but again at least in the high end game, most mages will find they aren't limited by mana pool but rather aggro. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I love having the Elemental forms.  I love the Air for the resists and Levitate.  It's very nice having a levitate that adds to my resists and lasts that long for no mana.  Worth it for me.
<br />
Water form's regen is a bonus in indoor zones.  Another 4 mana/tic is very nice and should not be scoffed at.  Not all mages are elemental mages with the best gear, but any mages that levels up can buy this.  I would deem this a great AA and very usefull.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Fury of Magic : Ok, this one is useful also. More chances are crits are always nice to have. but it's shared by all int casters so it's nto a class AA. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Usefull?  How about fantastic?  Beyond saving me mana, increasing my DPS, and impressing my friends it's very fun.  I'm very happy to have level 3 of this AA.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Hastened Mending : Yes and no, it can be useful if you like healing pets, but eh... 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
9 min between free pet heals for 2146 is already super to have, but they are instant cast heals too.  Meaning I can be kiting 2 mobs and click my pet back to full health while he tanks a 3rd mob.  Or I can be paying attention to my nuke DPS on a boss mob and then see my pet enrage and click his HP back to 55% before the next AoE goes off.  9 min between cycles is fantastic and you are being way too negative.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Host of the Elements : Outclassed by shaman swarm pets. Making them half the number of our swarm but half the recast time makes them even, but add in they're higher level (so hit more and have more hp) but they enrage also and it's fairly obvious to see.. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
So what if Shamans have this ability to and maybe better!  It's a great ability and it has allowed me to kill mobs I could not kill before.  Any ability that increases your power like that is very valuable.  Especially for caster mobs, this can be really good as 9 zerg pets will push that sucker all over the place.
<br />

<br />
I know you are trying to make a point, but I think you are going overboard to be negative about many of these AA.  It gives less credibility to the rest of your post.  Some of these AA you bagged on are very good AA and I have been extremely pleased with them.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
